Insider Activity


Individual




Gregory P. Spivy



Mr. Gregory P. Spivy is a Partner at ValueAct Capital Management LP. He is the Chairman and Director of Seitel, Inc., and a Director of Allison Transmission Holdings, Inc. and Armstrong World Industries, Inc.
Prior to joining ValueAct Capital in September 2004, Mr. Spivy worked with Gryphon Investors, a private equity fund with $500 million in investments. Previously, he was a Managing Director at Fremont Partners (“Fremont”), a private equity firm. Prior to joining Fremont, Mr. Spivy was a Director with The Bridgeford Group, and began his career in the mergers and acquisitions department of Lehman Brothers. He was the former chairman of MSD Performance, Inc. and a former director of MDS, Inc., MSC Software Corp., PRA International and KAR Auction Services, Inc.
Mr. Spivy received his BA degree from Northwestern University.



