Gregory Paul Spivy: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 6:04 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Lehman Brothers - Equities Division



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Gregory Paul Spivy  Associate, Lehman Brothers - Equities DivisionAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 13 Board Members in 13 different organizations across 18 different industries.See Board Relationships48--
Background

		Mr. Gregory Paul Spivy, also known as Greg, serves as a Partner of ValueAct Capital, LLC. Mr. Spivy joined ValueAct Capital, LLC. in September 2004. Mr. Spivy serves as an Associate of Lehman Brothers - Equities Division. Mr. Spivy served at Gryphon Investors. He served as Managing Director at Fremont Partners. He served as Managing Director of Calera Capital. He served as an Associate of Lehman Brothers in the equity capital department, where Mr. Spivy was responsible ... for the origination, development and execution of equity and equity related new issues. He spent the first two years of his career in the mergers and acquisition department at Lehman Brothers. Mr. Spivy has been the Chairman at N360x, L.L.C. since October 24, 2011. He served as Chairman of Seitel Inc. until January 19, 2017. He served as Chairman of MSD Performance, Inc. He served as Chairman and Director of Autotronic Controls Corporation. He has been a Director of ADESA Ohio, LLC since April 2007. He has been a Director of ADESA Corporation, LLC since April 2007. He has been a Director of Seitel Solutions and Seitel Data Corp., Seitel Delaware, Inc since March 2006. He has been a Director of Vision Energy, Inc. (DDD Energy Inc.) since March 2006. He serves on the Board of Directors of The Kerr Group, Inc. He has been a Director of Adesa Indianapolis, Inc since April 2007. He has been a Director of Insurance Auto Auctions, Inc. since April 2007. He serves as a Director of ADESA, Inc. He has been a Director of Seitel, Inc. since March 1, 2006. He has been a Director of Auto Dealers Exchange of Memphis, LLC since April 2007. He has been an Independent Director of Armstrong World Industries, Inc. since December 15, 2014. He served as a Director of Allison Transmission Holdings, Inc. since May 14, 2015 until May 11, 2017. He served as a Director of Nordion (Canada) Inc. until June 2010. Prior to joining Fremont Partners in 1995, Mr. Spivy served as a Director of The Bridgeford Group, Inc. He served as a Director of KAR Auction Services, Inc. from April 2007 to December 16, 2013. He served as a Director of Nordion Inc. since April 2008. He served as a Director of MDS, Inc. and PRA International. Mr. Spivy served as a Director of MSC Software Corporation from December 6, 2004 to May 26, 2006 and PRA Health Sciences, Inc. until June 2007. Mr. Spivy has a B.A. in Economics from Northwestern University, graduating magna cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa.Read Full Background




